caption: Green papaya salad and mani dished are recommended
Authentic excellent cuisine. Service was on par with the finest restaurants any where in the world
amazing food, unique menu, and warm atmosphere!

Great place. Awesome food. Had Duc himself wait on our table, the best customer service anywhere around. If you're looking to treat your significant other to a great experience and awesome ambiance. This is the place. You won't regret the money spent.
Amazing!
Literally the best

Omg! As an experience chef and hungry girl Duc's Bistro is a must for anyone visiting Honolulu! French influence Vietnamese pairings are on point, and true to Hawaiian culture plates are able to be shared! Family owned and operated for 28 years strong is tribute to the quality served here. My husband and I had the escargot, pork belly,  lamb, and both dessert specials! All were to die for. Best dinning experience we've had in our 2 weeks here!
Great food! Delicious steak tartare, pork belly, daily specials and entrees. Very intimate setting and a personal greeting and service. Would 100% recommend for an authentic experience.
A family run, white table cloth french vietnamese restaurant with great food, atmosphere, and priced right. We had an excellent time.
The food is incredible and Duc is an amazing host

I loved every bite, twice this month! Fois gras is my favorite appetizer, yet it is rare to find. Flavor combinations were surprising, sour to sweet. Salty to savory. We ordered a 4 course meal. Went back weeks later, and ordered 4 different courses. Too much info to type. No matter what you order, if you love good food, You’ll be in the right spot!
Excellent food and service  !!!
Way overpriced for the tiny portions of food. Followed the recommendations and left with a $300 bill for family of four. Won’t be back again.
Hard to say which is better the food or the staff, both are excellent!
Absolutely fantastic.

We chose Duc’s Bistro for our first meal out after three months in quarantine! It was wide open and safe as can be. Duc is the best! The crispy fish done Vietnamese style was flavorful and delicious. The catch of the day was mahi-mahi in a caper lemon butter sauce, French style. Both were fantastic!  The saffron rice and French style green beans with garlic were tasty too.  We couldn’t eat all of the duck pate and 4 mini baguettes, all of which were delicious, so they let us pack them up to take home, and even included some ginger pickles and cilantro at no charge. What a fabulous brunch we had today!  Welcome back,Duc!  Please consider offering you Vietnamese bun bowls again! They would make great carry out for lunch or dinner!  You used to offer a bowl with julienne of super crisp greens and apple, topped with your choice of fresh fish, grilled pork or lemon grass chicken skewers dressed in a very light sweet and sour dressing. Yumm!  The best anyone could make anywhere outside of Vietnam!  Your wine list and bar selections are fantastic too!  We’ll be back again soon!
Best foie gra on the island!
Absolute best
Delicious. Best food I have had in years! So good.
Excellent service and food. Great for a romantic dinner or special occasion. Will definitely be back.

This is a stellar find - one of those "best kept secret" places. Just a small,  wonderful French Vietnamese restaurant with subtle, flavorful dishes that can surprise you in the best way. Every dish was something special. Leave room for the amazing desserts.
Fancy and Fun
Fabulous food and great ambiance.  A hidden GEM!
Detailed setting, distinctly delicious duck, steak, foie gras and shrimp. You must leave room for the owner made special cheese cake.
Good food in an unusual location!
Lemon grass chicken was good, crab cakes was a smaller portion than I expected but it was delicious. Beer n wine selection is unusually limited to non local brands.
Exquisite authentic Vietnamese restaurant.
Awesome food and service
Such a wonderful experience being served by the owner, treated like royalty. Very high quality food, all made from scratch. A real treat, and a gem of a restaurant - we will be sure to be back!

Duck's Bistro is a quaint little restaurant in China town that serves the most delicious dishes.   The service is awesome and they make you feel at home.   Everything was amazing as you can see we couldn't wait to try the escargots.  I would highly recommend this place.

Very small portion sizes for the cost. Was good food but would not justify for the price. I went in for the lunch so I'm not sure if they skimped out during the lunch but would say save your money for somewhere else. I did go somewhere else after and get more food right after
Food was great service excellent. A little warm.
Delicious vietnamese food with a twist of french cousine. And the service was excellent.
A hidden gem in Honolulu Chinatown.

Had the crab cake, beef tartar, and spring rolls for appetizers. Lamb chops and Grand Marnier duck for main dishes, with a side of asparagus for a vegetable. For our desert, we selected a sampling of Belle de Brillet and St Germain Liquors from the bar.  The meal was great, service was excellent, and atmosphere being pleasantly comforting. The attentiveness to our inquisitive curiosity, asking about choices and recommendations, was refreshing. A definite recommend and will have to revisit to try other menu choices.
Cozy,  family style,  and romantic. Attentive staff

Duc's is located  in the Chinatown area right around the corner from the new American Savings Bank building. Nice decor for a more laid back than formal vibe.  There's even a "hidden door" to a closet for storing booze!  Food served family style, as it says on the menu. Makes it easy to order different items with friends and everyone gets to try everything, sharing is caring people! There's a pork dish that was amazing, it looks like a slab of bacon, but you literally eat it with a spoon, nuff said. Other choices were also good grinds.  Staff was very friendly and made us feel at home shortly after sitting down. I would recommend Duc's and will be returning for another go at the menu.
Broad range of elegant Vietnamese dishes, all very good. A family restaurant with a long history and tradition of consistently serving the freshest most innovative Vietnamese dishes.
Good ambience byt food was underwhelming
Best Food in Chinatown
Very good food.
Amazing small,  elegant restaurant with some of the best food in town.

Duc's Bistro is always a good choice when you're looking for an excellent meal!  We've been there so many times,  we don't even order!  He brings us his specials which we share family style. And everything is delicious!!!
Every time we go to Duc's is an incredible experience. The food is incredibly delicious and varied, the cocktails are fantastic, and the service is warm and personal.

Please do not pass through Honolulu without having dinner at this restaurant! We ate family style so we could all sample broadly. There was not a single disappointment! The rack of lamb melted in my mouth! The pan fried Basso fish was delicate and flavorful. The fire roasted eggplant was exotically seasoned. The iced coffee, cheese cake, and tapioca were fabulous! This place is a must!
Great food and very friendly service. Would be a 5 but it was a little slow..

Was here for my Sister In-laws birthday party. Foods are delicious. Love their spring rolls and salad. Onaga fish can't beat the flavor. Warm and friendly environment. Service is excellent. Deffinitely going back some other time.
Very impressed
Delightful restaurant. Food is delicious, lovingly prepared, freshest ingredients. Service is impeccable. Ambiance cannot be beat. Family who own and run this are gracious and capable.
One of the best restaurants in Honolulu it's a family business and the owners are truly special and so is the food

Great tasting authentic vietnamese and french cuisine.  I recommend the xhicken curry (simplified name, sorry).  Excellent staff and service which is most likely due to the fact that it is family run.  If you park in the car park across the street let the restaurant know which bay number you are in and they will sort of the parking fee.
Great atmosphere, great food, a favorite!
Great atmosphere and friendly family staff!
The ambience was warm and inviting. We're definitely going back.

Quality blend of vietnamese ingredients and french cooking techniques. The Basa (white fish) was cooked perfectly and was delicious. Their cocktail selection is also very good. The restaurant is on the pricy side for Chinatown.
An amazing night! Wonderful little gem in Chinatown! They have been here for the last 27 years!
John Lin took me here
Excellent! Always excellent!
Always empty when I go there but the food and Service are definitely worth 5 stars.
Good to have some drinks after sunset! They have nice hummus platter. Little bit overpriced but you pay for the view and the experience.
Another wonderful evening at Duc's Bistro. Duc and his family make you feel your part of the ohana. Excellent service and delicious food. A great place for a date night or a group event.
Hidden gem in Chinatown. Great host and food. Parking across the street.
Awesome
I love this place! Still trying to make my way thru the menu and haven't had anything that wasn't top notch delicious!
Amazing quality and service.  Absolutely the best meal I’ve had in a very very long time.

Very impressed by the flavors, attentiveness of the staff & quality of the food! Nice quiet & romantic setting. Not like most of the downtown restraunts that are quite clamorous. The pomelo salad had subtle floral undertones, the crab cakes were full of flavorful crab meat and topped with a delicious creamy sauce & the green mango pan fried fish was unique & filling.

Spent about $30 per person, but others could easily get away with less. Service was far above par. They were very friendly. Food was great: chicken curry, lemongrass chicken, lemongrass tofu, ginger fantastic,  steak, saffron rice, mojito, mint tea, tomato lobster bisque, crab cakes, duck pate, and banana blossom salad. The entire group complimented. High praise were given from our vegetarian with multiple food issues (no gluten, no dairy, no mushrooms, no corn). The surrounding area was pitiful making Duc's Bistro a diamond in a haystack.
Foie Gras was cooked to perfection and very good.  The seared duck was very tender, however was not very flavorful
Wonderful Vietnamese food, atmosphere, and staff.

Elegant but comfortable family-run restaurant serving Vietnamese French style cuisine. The food is sublime, the service gracious, and the atmosphere is relaxed and restful. Cannot be beat for a special occasion out.
Amazing food, helpful and happy staff. Restaraunt  has a quiet and romantic atmosphere, the food was delicious and more than reasonably priced. Glad I found this gem for a much needed date night.
An amazing restaurant! Mr Duc and his wife run the place. Very friendly. Terrific service! Highly recommended!! Foodies will love this place!
Great Vietnamese cuisine in a formal atmosphere in the heart of a China town.
Amazing
Enjoyed it immensely.
Excellent staff and service. Meet Duc if you can..he is a charm. The food is top notch..great wine...very friendly and totally authentic. You won't be disappointed.

I was expecting more, don't get me wrong, the server and staff are very friendly but the portion is unbelievable. We pay for 2 small and I mean very small  that consist of 2 piece of fish over sauce and maybe 3 piece of chicken with curey plates and I had the madam vue  drink came up to a total of $64.00? Really??? Wish I had taken a picture. First and last. Thank you!
Superb experience, food and strolling singer too
food was delicious!
Kind of an unusual combination of Vietnamese and French cuisine. Family style portions.
I personally like delicacies like tartare and foie gras. You must have a developed palette to fully enjoy it here. Great ambiance with quiet music.
Duc's always a nice owner.  We just tell him to bring us what he wants to cook and never disappoints!

The best kept secret treasure in Honolulu. We went on a Wednesday night when Rachel Gonzales was singing - wow! It was such pleasant surprise - she's fantastic - loved her voice, arrangements & choice of music. Food and service were also excellent. Our new favorite place.
Honestly my favorite place in Honolulu, give it a try. The salads are to die for, drinks are great. The atmosphere makes you feel at home.
Excellent food for a very reasonable price
Excellent food.  Great service.  Quiet, warm and inviting atmosphere.  Owner and staff are very friendly.  Family style menu makes sampling a wide variety of their menu possible.

Quiet little place with a super friendly and informative staff who helped us figure out how to order as all the dishes are served "family style." The food was all amazing as were the drinks. Highly recommend for a date night or couples get-together.
A very unique spot in the middle of chaina town.  Great food, amazing ambiance, and a very classy spot.  The drinks are great, service is amazing, and the dishes are perfect.
Great service, great food!

Family owned and operated for over 20 years.  Six of us shared 3 appetizers, 5 entrees, and 5 desserts family style and we loved ALL of them! They took allergies and dietary restrictions in to consideration when preparing the wonderful "chef's choice" menu.  Can't wait until we return.

It's an upscale Vietnamese restaurant with a pleasant atmosphere that doesn't have the typical pho or banh mi sandwiches. It wasn't crowded when I went and I was seated right away. The service was very professional. We had Mousse of Black Truffle Duck Paté  and chicken curry to share between two people. The quantity was just right and appetizing. I would consider coming back on a special occasion.
Delicious Vietnamese and French cuisine here
(Translated by Google) Vietnamese French is delicious!  (Original) ベトナムフレンチって美味しい！
I ate there 5 nights in a row. Tried everything on their menu. Guess what? It was all phenomenal!
Upscale place with family-style servings. The chef is fantastic and very friendly, coming to each table.
I've been here twice and loved both times.  The food was very tasty, and is a great value.  Get past the exterior and be pleasantly surprised!
